data.meta_description: Otto Ping (1883-1975) was an amateur photographer who captured life around Brown County from 1900-1940. While he took photographs he worked as a peddler, farmer, and canner in the area. He photographed individuals, couples, and family groups, as well as farms, their animals and implements. This book contains a selection of his photographs with commentary by W. Douglas Hartley and essays by Anne E. Peterson and Stephen J. Fletcher.
